        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Memorandum of cattle collected for Austin.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>A memorandum of Cattle Collected of [for] <persName>Col. S F Austin</persName> out of
the stock that sd. <persName>Austin </persName>bought of <persName>Rabbs</persName></p>

<p><date when="1832-05-01">May 1st 1832 </date> </p>
<p>one brindle steer which had been worked some little
which steer I sold to <persName>J. Parker</persName>___________  $25 00</p>

<p>one three year old steer which sold to <persName>Parker </persName>at 10___    10 00</p>

<p><date when="1832-06-01">June 1st</date>   one white steer which I sold to <persName>James Cox</persName>___    20 00</p>
<p>10 00    55 00</p>
<p>one old cow that runs at <persName>A Castleman</persName>______________    </p>
<p>"   young   unbroke   cow   that   runs   at   <placeName><persName>M.  Allen</persName>'s</placeName></p>

<p><date when="1832-10-20">Oct. 20th </date>     which I sold to <persName>Father</persName>________   10 00</p>

<p>one black cow and one 2 year old bull (this cow you
got of <persName>Kelly Mc.Farland </persName>the calf died or was
killed <date n="SPring - 1832">last spring</date>) these cattle I let <persName>Father </persName>have
which was valued at 17________    17 00</p>
<p>7 00   37 00</p>
<p>The same cows yearling bull which I keep to run     
with  my  cattle   these   bull   have  no   marks   or
brands but will some times suck the cow and of
course they must be yours</p>
<p>one white yearlin which I sold to <persName>father </persName>of the stock
of <persName>Rabbs</persName>_______________    5 00</p>

<p>104 00</p>

<p>[Indorsed:]</p>

<p>A memorandum of Cattle which I collected of <persName>Col S F Austin</persName>
<date n="10-xx-1832">October 1832 </date>By <persName>Thos. H Borden</persName></p>



        </div1>
